Smoove is a French company that designs, manufactures and markets products related to bike-sharing. The company produces lightweight bike stands that require virtually no civil engineering and no electricity. The lock is on the bicycle, situated in the fork. It secures the bike in the stations and outside the stations with an auto-winding cable.
The system won some recognition by mayors and in the industry for its reliability, its moderate price and the fact that it is not linked to an advertising deal.


